  "text": "Etiological treatment in case of accidents with material contaminated with parasites or blood samples of patients infected with T. cruzi could also be considered as an indication for primary prevention. Actually, the treatment is not strictly a prophylaxis because it is not possible to avoid the infections, but the infection can be aborted immediately after accidents with a timely treatment to get an appropriate concentration of specific drugs (recommendation (B), and evidence III) [CITATION_1] .",
